source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Print the minimum size a device can be shrunk to.

Returns the minimum size in bytes that the specified device can be resized to
without losing data. The device id 1 is used by default. Requires CAP_SYS_ADMIN
(unless --offline is used).

Usage: min-dev-size [OPTIONS] <PATH>

Arguments:
  <PATH>
          Path to a file or directory on the btrfs filesystem, or a block device
          / image file when --offline is used

Options:
      --id <DEVID>
          Specify the device id to query
          
          [default: 1]

      --offline
          Read directly from an unmounted device or image file instead of a
          mounted filesystem. Does not require CAP_SYS_ADMIN

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
